The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 27 December is 140,598 (16,204.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 22 December, there were 8,594 new confirmed cases (990.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 15 December, there were 6,196 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 39% (2,398 extra cases).
